helptext="The Transport Helicopter carries troops into battle. Its attack against units on land is a bombard attack. Against units on water it has a regular attack.","Helicopters can transport military land units. While most troops must load or unload in a city, airstrip, or airbase, units specializing in mobility can embark or disembark at any time.","Unlike other aircraft, Helicopters are not required to return to a city, base, or Carrier to refuel after a set number of turns. However, care must be exercised, due to the health they lose every turn."

